<h2> IoT Security Research</h2>
<p>See this <a href="https://iotsecurity.eecs.umich.edu">page </a> for research in our group on IoT and Cyber-Physical Systems. Some recent work includes research on robust physical perturbation attacks on  machine learning classifers (CVPR 2018), defense mechanisms to make OAuth tokens at trigger-action cloud services such as IFTTT less risky (NDSS 2018), security analysis of SmartThings IoT application platform (IEEE S&P 2016), and ContexIoT, an automatic IoT app patching mechanism to help enforce context-based permissions (NDSS 2017).
</p>


